c: 5
v: 18
t: "The Jews and Christians assert, \"We are God’s children and His beloved ones.\" Say: \"Why, then, does He punish you for your sins? No. You are but mortals that (just like others) He has created. He forgives whom He wills, and He punishes whom He wills. To God belongs the sovereignty of the heavens and the earth and all that is between them, and to Him is the homecoming"